Postman - API testing tool
We can do manual testing of API's using postman

Workspace : area where we maintain files and saved.
Create a new workspace
Create a new collection : collection contains folders and requests

Request-->API-->Response

Get : Retrieve the resource from server
Post : Create resource on database
Put : Update existing resource on database
Patch : Update partial details of resource
Delete :  Delete existing resource from database

Validations :
1. Status code
2. Time
3. Size data
4. Response Body (json/xml)
5. Cookies
6. Headers

http status codes:
3 levels of status codes
200:OK
201:Created
202:Non-Authoritative Information
204:No Content

400:Bad Request
401:Unauthorized
403:Forbidden
404:Not Found
409:Conflict

500:Internal Server Error
501:Not Implemented
502:Bad Gateway
503:Service Unavailable
504:Gateway Timeout
599:Network Timeout


